cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on object search in cluttered scenes using a manipulation planner for robotics applications. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses a deep neural network for shape completion to infer the geometry of occluded objects. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the performance of the manipulation planner. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a deep neural network for shape completion. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a volumetric memory system used in the manipulation planner.
